            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_9yPipQ": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Balanced skin stays comfortable through most of the day. It isn't tight after washing, doesn't flake, and doesn't shine much beyond perhaps a little across the nose. It takes most products in its stride and rarely stings or flares. If you're a touch oilier in the T-zone and drier on the cheeks, that combination usually sits here too.<br/><br/>If your skin mostly just gets on with things, you're in the right place. If you're not sure, the <a href=\"/pages/find-your-skin-type\" title=\"Find Your Skin Type\">skin type finder</a> takes a couple of minutes.<br/></p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_ECWcka": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>What this skin type needs</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h3",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_hiULWP": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Balanced skin is the one that's easy to overlook, precisely because it behaves. It doesn't need rescuing, and the commonest mistake is doing too much to it. What it wants is light, unfussy hydration that keeps it comfortable, plus a little antioxidant support to help protect it over the longer term. The research points to antioxidants as a sensible, low-drama way to look after skin that's already in good shape.<br/><br/>Balanced skin can drift toward dry or oily with age, season or a change in routine, so the quiet aim is simply to keep it where it is. Support, not control, as ever.<br/></p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_7Ck6rn": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The oils we chose for it</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h3",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_kfnJJB": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Every Balanced moisturiser shares the same even blend of five cold-pressed organic oils, chosen for this skin type and carried at a different richness in each of the three textures. This is the most balanced blend we make, five oils at the same weight.<br/><br/><a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/jojoba-seed-simmondsia-chinensis-seed-oil\" title=\"Simmondsia Chinensis (Jojoba) Seed Oil\">Jojoba</a>, a liquid wax unusually close to the skin's own sebum, suits skin you want to keep just as it is. <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/rose-hip-rosa-canina-seed-oil\" title=\"Rosa Canina (Rose Hip) Fruit Oil\">Rose hip</a> is light and high in linoleic acid, the essential fatty acid the skin draws on to keep its barrier in order. <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/pomegranate-punica-granatum-seed-oil\" title=\"Punica Granatum (Pomegranate) Seed Oil\">Pomegranate</a> brings punicic acid and antioxidant polyphenols. <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/baobob-adansonia-digitata-seed-oil\" title=\"Adansonia Digitata (Baobab) Seed Oil\">Baobab</a> adds stable, conditioning fatty acids and sterols. And <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/dragon-fruit-hylocereus-undatus-seed-oil\" title=\"Hylocereus Undatus (Dragon Fruit) Fruit Extract\">dragon fruit</a> seed oil rounds the blend out with a light, well-balanced profile.<br/><br/>Around those five sits a supporting cast shared across the whole range. <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/squalane\" title=\"Squalane\">Squalane</a>, a lightweight oil close to one the skin makes for itself. Soothing <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/allantoin\" title=\"Allantoin\">allantoin</a>. A prebiotic and postbiotic pairing chosen to support the skin's own microbiome, where the evidence is still emerging and we would rather say so than overstate it. And our signature <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/bladder-wrack-fucus-vesiculosus-extract\" title=\"Fucus Vesiculosus (Bladderwrack) Extract\">bladderwrack</a>, the same Atlantic seaweed species we know from the rocks below Welcombe, though the extract itself is produced in France from that species. The coast is the kinship here, not the supply chain.<br/><br/>Every ingredient, and the exact amount of each, is published on each product page. That's the whole point of how we work, and each one links through to its own page if you want to read further.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_NkE9Xj": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Your three moisturisers</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h3",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_cTGRCz": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The same Balanced blend comes in three textures, so you can match the richness to where you're using it.<br/><br/><strong>Flow </strong>is the lightest, made for the face. <strong>Core </strong>is richer and more cushioning, for the body. <strong>Deep </strong>is the richest, for the areas that turn driest, the hands, elbows and feet.<br/><br/>Same blend throughout. More or less of it, depending on what the skin is asking for.</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
