        "text_ahKGbw": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>The main thing with balanced skin is not to overthink it.<br/><br/>Keep the routine simple and consistent, and resist the urge to pile on strong actives your skin doesn't actually need, since that's the quickest way to upset a good balance. Cleanse gently, moisturise to stay comfortable, and give your skin a little antioxidant support and sensible sun protection to help keep it the way it is. That's genuinely most of it. Balanced skin rewards a light touch more than a busy one.<br/><br/>You'll have noticed we never use synthetic fragrance. There's a single essential oil in the range, <a href=\"/blogs/ingredients/vetiver-vetiveria-zizanioides-root-oil\" title=\"Vetiveria Zizanoides (Vetiver) Root Oil\">vetiver</a>, at a low level and chosen on purpose, and it appears on every label so you can see exactly how much is there.<br/></p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_iiUCEX": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.heading",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Your skin can settle over time</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "h3",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
            "line_height": "normal",
            "letter_spacing": "normal",
            "case": "none",
            "wrap": "pretty",
            "text_color": "",
            "background": false,
            "background_color": "#00000026",
            "corner_radius": 0,
            "padding-block-start": 0,
            "padding-block-end": 0,
            "padding-inline-start": 0,
            "padding-inline-end": 0
          },
          "blocks": {}
        },
        "text_hVYV6M": {
          "type": "text",
          "name": "t:names.text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "<p>Balanced skin sits in a good place, but it isn't fixed there. It can drift toward dry or oily with age, environment, health or a change in routine. The reassuring part is that steady, gentle care tends to keep it where it is, and if it does shift, kind and consistent care can help bring it back toward the middle over time. It's gradual, and it comes from looking after your skin steadily rather than from any single product working magic. If your skin changes, the skin type finder is always there to place yourself again</p>",
            "width": "fit-content",
            "max_width": "normal",
            "alignment": "left",
            "type_preset": "rte",
            "font": "var(--font-body--family)",
            "font_size": "1rem",
